#1

(This is a continuation of this thread.)

Inspired by Mero’s fantastic website www.footyjumpers.com, this thread shall illustrate the jerseys worn in the NRL from its foundation in 1908.​

Notes

1. Accuracy is not 100% as information prior to the 1990s is difficult to obtain. If you notice any errors, please free to message me with corrections.

2. Unless otherwise specified, the jersey/uniform in each image was worn in every match in the year(s) stated. Prior to 1994, uniforms are listed if they were worn that year; specific matches are not known and some may have only been worn in preseason games.

3. After the year(s) is the jersey manufacturer (where known). Manufacturers are unknown prior to the 1970s.

4. Until the early 1990s, many players wore jerseys with cut ¾ length sleeves, as opposed to actual ½ length sleeves. Overlaps in years is when both ½ and ¾ length sleeves were made and worn by players on a team.

5. Sponsors are not featured, primarily due to the difficulty in getting quality images of their logos.

6. Until the 1970s, black shorts often faded to grey.

#2

Newtown Jets

1908–1949* — Original uniform with number panel and darker blue socks

1950*–1975 — Number panel removed, socks now match jersey colour

* Exact year these changes occurred is unknown

1976 — (Westmont) ¾ length sleeves with three stripes around elbows

1977 — (Westmont) Vee-neck collar, stripes added to sides of shorts and tops of socks

1978 — (Westmont) New team logo

1979–1982 — (Classic) Collar, lighter blue, longer ¾ sleeves with thinner stripes and white cuffs, stripes on shorts and socks reduced to two

1979–1982, alternate — (Classic) Blue shorts were worn in various matches, both home and away, usually against Souths and Easts

#4

South Sydney Rabbitohs

1908 — Original fourteen stripes jersey, to differentiate from the South Sydney union team

1909–1914 — Wider myrtle stripes, same as original pre-League jersey (sock colour uncertain)

1915–1944 — Socks changed (colour uncertain)

1945–1946 — Wartime jersey

1947–1958 — Back to traditional design, new socks (number panel uncertain, may have been white number without panel)

1959–1961 — “Saddle” jersey, lace-up collar, rabbit emblem, white shorts (number panel uncertain, may have been white number without panel)

1962–1964 — Wider stripes on socks (number panel uncertain, may have been white number without panel)

1965–1968 — Back to traditional design, with rabbit emblem, four red stripes on body,

1969–1974 — Five red stripes on body

1975 — (Westmont) Green shorts, ¾ length sleeves, more stripes on socks

1976 — (Westmont) Sleeve stripes moved, wider stripes on socks, number lowered to accommodate sponsor

1977 — (Classic) Red vee-neck collar, longer ¾ sleeves

1978 — (Classic) New team logo, different shorts

1979 — (Classic) Logo repositioned, red cuffs on sleeves

early 1980 — (Classic) “Minties” jersey, yellow number

later 1980 (Classic) — Not long into the season, a green panel with white number(s) was added due to visibility issues with the yellow number(s)

1981–1982 — (Classic) Stripe removed from back

Eastern Suburbs Tri-colours / Roosters

1908–1932 — Original uniform, stripes varied

1920 — Temporary replacement jersey worn in Rounds 4 to 8

1933–1943 — Red stripe wider

1944–1946 — Wartime jersey, navy dye was prioritised to the Navy

1947–1953 — Back to 1933 design, all jerseys had white-over-red stripes

1954–1966 — New uniform, inspired by the then-popular French national team

1967–1973 — Team emblem added

1974–1975 — ¾ length sleeves, some players had jerseys with longer sleeves and navy cuffs

1976 — Number lowered to accommodate sponsor

1977–1978 — Stripes added to sides of shorts

1979 — (Classic) Sleeves standardised

1980–1982 — Team name added to badge

1982 — (Classic) Summer uniform worn in Rounds 1–3

In 1979 to 1983 Penrith wore Brown collars on both white versions and Brown versions. From 1984 to 1990 Penrith wore white collars on both White version and Brown Version, there was never any blue collars in 1979. Here are the ones from 1979 to 1982. In 1979 the White version was in all games. from 1980 to 1982 the Brown version is the main Uniform and the White version is clash ones.
